#week-title("Two", "The Ten Sephiroth & Alchemical Correspondences")

=== Core Teaching

The ten sephiroth of the Tree correspond to the ten digits — and to the ten
aspects of the One Creative Energy. Each sphere has a specific alchemical meaning:

- *Kether (1):* The Crown; the original unity; the prima materia.
- *Chokmah (2):* Wisdom; the volatile principle; Sulphur in its highest aspect.
- *Binah (3):* Understanding; the fixed principle; Salt in its highest aspect.
- *Tiphereth (6):* Beauty; the Sun; the alchemical gold.
- *Yesod (9):* Foundation; the Moon; the vehicle of subtle forces (dew).
- *Malkuth (10):* Kingdom; the Earth; the body and the physical laboratory.

=== Topics This Week

- The ten spheres as stages of manifestation
- Planetary correspondences of the sephiroth
- Locating your ongoing Work on the Tree

#inner-work[
  *Path Meditation*

  For Week 2, meditate with *The High Priestess (Key 2)*. This card represents
  hidden knowledge and the *Philosophic Mercury*. Observe the blue and white tones
  and the scroll in her lap. How does this imagery relate to your receptivity in
  the laboratory?

  Record your insights in your Tarot journal.
